# Meal Prep Website Build Prompt

<goal>
Create a structured React-based website that presents a comprehensive meal prep system, focusing on systematic organization and clear user pathways.
</goal>

<context>
The system is based on a 1-2-3 framework for meal rotation, utilizing standardized prep methods, precise container organization, and quality control measures.
</context>

<requirements>
- Use only Tailwind core utility classes
- Implement shadcn/ui components
- Focus on mobile-first responsive design
- Ensure clear navigation between system components
</requirements>

<pages>
<page id="home">
<title>Meal Prep Operating System</title>
<purpose>Introduce the systematic approach to meal preparation</purpose>
<key_elements>
- Hero section explaining the 1-2-3 framework
- Quick navigation to key system components
- Visual representation of the weekly timeline
- Overview of core principles
</key_elements>
</page>

<page id="framework">
<title>Core Framework</title>
<purpose>Detail the fundamental structure of the meal prep system</purpose>
<key_elements>
- Weekly schedule breakdown
- Meal slot system explanation
- Container organization guide
- Rotation system visualization
</key_elements>
</page>

<page id="equipment">
<title>Container System</title>
<purpose>Outline required equipment and organization methods</purpose>
<key_elements>
- Container specifications and purposes
- Storage layout recommendations
- Organization system details
- Maintenance protocols
</key_elements>
</page>

<page id="preparation">
<title>Prep Workflow</title>
<purpose>Guide users through the preparation process</purpose>
<key_elements>
- Timeline visualization
- Step-by-step prep guide
- Tips and troubleshooting
- Quality control measures
</key_elements>
</page>

<page id="recipes">
<title>Base Recipes</title>
<purpose>Provide core recipes and variations</purpose>
<key_elements>
- Protein preparations
- Carbohydrate bases
- Vegetable preparations
- Sauce systems
</key_elements>
</page>

<style_guidelines>
<colors>
- Primary: slate-900
- Secondary: emerald-600
- Accent: amber-500
- Background: slate-50
- Text: slate-700
</colors>

<typography>
- Headers: font-bold text-2xl (desktop) text-xl (mobile)
- Subheaders: font-semibold text-xl (desktop) text-lg (mobile)
- Body: text-base leading-relaxed
- Navigation: text-sm font-medium
</typography>

<spacing>
- Section padding: p-6 (mobile) p-8 (desktop)
- Component gaps: gap-4 (mobile) gap-6 (desktop)
- Content max-width: max-w-7xl mx-auto
</spacing>
</style_guidelines>

<components>
<component id="navigation">
<type>Primary navigation bar</type>
<features>
- Mobile-responsive menu
- Current page indicator
- Quick access to key sections
</features>
</component>

<component id="page-header">
<type>Consistent page header</type>
<features>
- Title
- Brief description
- Navigation breadcrumbs
</features>
</component>

<component id="content-card">
<type>Information card template</type>
<features>
- Consistent padding
- Optional icon
- Title and content areas
</features>
</component>

<component id="timeline">
<type>Visual timeline component</type>
<features>
- Day/time indicators
- Task descriptions
- Status markers
</features>
</component>
</components>

<layout>
<structure>
- Sticky header with navigation
- Main content area
- Optional sidebar for larger screens
- Footer with quick links
</structure>

<grid>
- Mobile: single column
- Tablet: two columns where appropriate
- Desktop: flexible grid system
</grid>
</layout>

<accessibility>
- Semantic HTML structure
- ARIA labels where needed
- Keyboard navigation support
- Color contrast compliance
</accessibility>

<performance>
- Lazy loading for images
- Code splitting by route
- Minimal initial bundle
- Optimized assets
</performance>
</prompt>